<paragraph id="8B8DA174FFA3CB2847977062FE83F877" blockId="6.[151,1437,1728,1970]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,1884,1945]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Remarks: Among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFA3CB2946907062FD2AF8A8" box="[448,653,1836,1862]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA3CB2946907062FD94F8A8" box="[448,563,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Atractides</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F325E1E4FFA3CB29446E7062FCD5F8A8" box="[830,882,1836,1862]" name="Italy" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFA3CB29442F7062FBA0F8A8" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1956" box="[895,1031,1836,1862]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anellatus">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA3CB29442F7062FBA0F8A8" box="[895,1031,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. anellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characteristic in the combination of a lineated integument and the excretory pore surrounded by a sclerite ring (Fig. 1 C). Three species with the same character combination are reported exlusively from Madeira: 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFA3CB2944E2703AFAD4F860" authority="(Lundblad, 1941)" baseAuthorityName="Lundblad" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[946,1395,1908,1934]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulanus">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA3CB2944E2703AFB3BF860" box="[946,1180,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Atractides insulanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA3DC85FFA3CB2943E0703AFACCF860" author="Lundblad, O." box="[1200,1387,1908,1934]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="93 - 96" refId="ref75460" refString="Lundblad, O. (1941) Neue Wassermilben aus Madeira. Vorlaufige Mitteilung. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 62 (1 - 2), 93 - 96." type="journal article" year="1941">Lundblad, 1941</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFA3CB2942D4703AFDA4F85C" authority="(Lundblad, 1941)" baseAuthorityName="Lundblad" baseAuthorityYear="1941" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macaronensis">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA3CB2942D4703AFE95F85C" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. macaronensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA3DC85FFA3CB29461370D6FE5CF85C" author="Lundblad, O." box="[323,507,1944,1970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="93 - 96" refId="ref75460" refString="Lundblad, O. (1941) Neue Wassermilben aus Madeira. Vorlaufige Mitteilung. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 62 (1 - 2), 93 - 96." type="journal article" year="1941">Lundblad, 1941</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFA3CB29451370D6FC09F85C" authority="(Lundblad, 1941)" baseAuthorityName="Lundblad" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[579,942,1944,1970]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maderensis">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA3CB29451370D6FD7BF85C" box="[579,732,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A maderensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA3DC85FFA3CB2945BC70D6FC02F85C" author="Lundblad, O." box="[748,933,1944,1970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="93 - 96" refId="ref75460" refString="Lundblad, O. (1941) Neue Wassermilben aus Madeira. Vorlaufige Mitteilung. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 62 (1 - 2), 93 - 96." type="journal article" year="1941">Lundblad, 1941</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. They differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFA3CB2943D470D6FAABF85C" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1956" box="[1156,1292,1944,1970]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anellatus">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA3CB2943D470D6FAABF85C" box="[1156,1292,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. anellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
variously in 
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA2CB2847C77012FF7BF89B" bold="true" box="[151,220,1884,1909]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 1:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFA2CB2847B17013FE0BF89B" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1956" box="[225,428,1885,1909]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anellatus">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFA2CB2847B17013FE0BF89B" box="[225,428,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Atractides anellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D346AFDFFA2CB2846E87013FE6CF89A" box="[440,459,1885,1908]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(I 302). A, I-L-5/6; B, palp; C, venter (genital setae omitted); D, genital field with setation. Scale bars: 100 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DA174FFADCB2747C777D9FCCEFE8B" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
proportions of I-L-5-6, palp segments P-2 and -4, and/or shape of coxae and the excretory pore ring, but the four species are probably representatives of a W Mediterranean-Macaronesian clade. The morphology of the Sicilian specimens is in good agreement with the diagnosis discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA3DC85FFADCB2744337791FBB5FF17" author="Gerecke, R." box="[867,1042,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="141 - 378" refId="ref74237" refString="Gerecke, R. (2003) The water mites of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) in the western Palaearctic region: a revision. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 138, 141 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.06 - 0.00051. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Gerecke (2003)</bibRefCitation>
- important morphological features are depicted in Figs 1-2. The (South)East European 
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFADCB2745B0764DFB5DFEF3" authority="(Motas &amp; Tanasachi, 1948)" baseAuthorityName="Motas &amp; Tanasachi" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[736,1274,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sokolowi">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFADCB2745B0764DFC19FEF3" box="[736,958,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Atractides sokolowi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA3DC85FFADCB27449D764DFB55FEF3" author="Motas, C. &amp; Tanasachi, J." box="[973,1266,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="152 - 169" refId="ref76325" refString="Motas, C. &amp; Tanasachi, J. (1948) Especes nouvelles et connues du genre Megapus Neuman (Hydrachnelles) trouvees dans les eaux souterraines. Annales scientifiques de la Universite de Jassy, 31, 152 - 169." type="journal article" year="1948">Motaş &amp; Tanasachi, 1948</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a further spe- cies combining a lineated integument and sclerotized excretory pore, is probably phylogenetically distant, with a very different, characteristically-shaped I-L-5/6 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA3DC85FFADCB2745EA7605FCF9FE8B" author="Gerecke, R." box="[698,862,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="141 - 378" refId="ref74237" refString="Gerecke, R. (2003) The water mites of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari: Parasitengona: Hygrobatidae) in the western Palaearctic region: a revision. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 138, 141 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.06 - 0.00051. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Gerecke 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DA174FFADCB2747977621FE5BFE43" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Habitat: Rhithrobiont. All records in the study area from sun-exposed streams at low to middle altitudes, 
<quantity id="4CCA0C91FFADCB27421D7621FF17FE43" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="170.0" valueMax="320.0" valueMin="20.0">20-320 m</quantity>
; at I 553 Int in the hyporheic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DA174FFADCB27479776F9FE30FDF7" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Distribution: West Mediterranean (Iberian Peninsula, 
<collectingCountry id="F325E1E4FFADCB27444876F9FC27FE3F" box="[792,896,439,465]" name="Morocco" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49F66F96FFADCB2744DA76F9FC77FE3C" box="[906,976,439,466]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Sicily</collectingRegion>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F325E1E4FFADCB2744AE76F9FB96FE3F" box="[1022,1073,439,465]" name="Italy" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Italy</collectingCountry>
restricted to 
<collectingRegion id="49F66F96FFADCB2743EF76F9FAA7FE3F" box="[1215,1280,439,465]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Sicily</collectingRegion>
- here with an interesting southwestern distribution, not a part of the generally more diverse limnofauna of the northern mountains. First record from 
<collectingCountry id="F325E1E4FFADCB27460D76B1FE35FDF7" box="[349,402,511,537]" name="Italy" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Italy</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DA174FFADCB2747C7710BFB4AF9B3" blockId="8.[151,1261,1605,1629]" box="[151,1261,1605,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFADCB2747C7710BFF7BF9B3" bold="true" box="[151,220,1605,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C32DAF7FFADCB2747B2710BFE09F9B3" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1956" box="[226,430,1605,1629]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anellatus">
<emphasis id="B9467D66FFADCB2747B2710BFE09F9B3" box="[226,430,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Atractides anellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D346AFDFFADCB2746EA710BFE69F9B2" box="[442,462,1605,1628]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
